    • Field Detail

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final java.lang.Integer UNKNOWN
        Unknown reason code returned from RegisterTerminalResponse's or UnregisterEvent's getCode(). Please report this so we can create a new static variable for you if you need it.

      • OTHER_REASON

        public static final java.lang.Integer OTHER_REASON
        Non-specific reason code - use getReason() to get more information on the cause of the RegisterTerminalResponse or UnregisterEvent. If there is a specific code you need a static final for, please let us know so we can separate it out from all the other codes that use OTHER_REASON.

      • INTERNAL_FAILURE

        public static final java.lang.Integer INTERNAL_FAILURE
        Internal failure caused the RegisterTerminalResponse or UnregisterEvent. All state associated with the station is cleaned up and the phone can be re-registered again after this type of failure.

      • NETWORK_TIME_OUT

        public static final java.lang.Integer NETWORK_TIME_OUT
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() or UnregisterEvent.getCode() if a network timeout caused the event.

      • NORMAL_REGISTER

        public static final java.lang.Integer NORMAL_REGISTER
        Indicates that the registration process was successful,.

      • NORMAL_UNREGISTER

        public static final java.lang.Integer NORMAL_UNREGISTER
        Indicates that the unregistration process was successful.

      • IDLE_UNREGISTER

        public static final java.lang.Integer IDLE_UNREGISTER
        Indicates that the unregistration process was aborted because the device is already IDLE.

      • PROGRESS_UNREGISTER

        public static final java.lang.Integer PROGRESS_UNREGISTER
        Indicates that the unregistration process was aborted because the unregistration is already in progress.

      • CLIENT_REQUESTED_UNREG

        public static final java.lang.Integer CLIENT_REQUESTED_UNREG
        Returned by UnregisterEvent.getCode() if the application requested unregistration.

      • CONNECTION_LOST_UNREG

        public static final java.lang.Integer CONNECTION_LOST_UNREG
        Returned by UnregisterEvent.getCode() if the link to Communication Manager is lost.

      • ADMIN_REQUESTED_UNREG

        public static final java.lang.Integer ADMIN_REQUESTED_UNREG
        Returned by UnregisterEvent.getCode() if the AE Services administrator reinitialized the device using the OAM.

      • INCORRENT_PASSWD_LOGIN

        public static final java.lang.Integer INCORRENT_PASSWD_LOGIN
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if a bad password/DeviceID combination was sent in the register request.

      • INVALID_EXTENSION

        public static final java.lang.Integer INVALID_EXTENSION
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if a non-existent extension on the switch was specified.

      • EXTENSION_IN_USE

        public static final java.lang.Integer EXTENSION_IN_USE
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if a the phone/extension is already registered with the switch and the forceLogin option was set to false. ForceLogin allows a phone/extension to be registered even if it is already registered. A forced registration supercedes any prior registration.

      • LIMIT_OF_CMAPI_PHONES_REACHED

        public static final java.lang.Integer LIMIT_OF_CMAPI_PHONES_REACHED
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if the limit of allowed CMAPI softphones has been reached, contact Avaya to purchase more IP_API licenses.

      • LIMIT_OF_IP_PHONE_LICENSES_REACHED

        public static final java.lang.Integer LIMIT_OF_IP_PHONE_LICENSES_REACHED
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if the limit of allowed IP phones has been reached. Contact Avaya to purchase more IP_API licenses.

      • CMAPI_NOT_LICENSED_ON_SWITCH

        public static final java.lang.Integer CMAPI_NOT_LICENSED_ON_SWITCH
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if the license file indicates that no IP_API licenses have been purchased. Please contact Avaya for a new license.

      • STATION_911SETTINGS_INVALID

        public static final java.lang.Integer STATION_911SETTINGS_INVALID
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if the 911 registration parameters did not match the 911 settings of the station on the switch.

      • NOT_SOFTPHONE_ENABLED

        public static final java.lang.Integer NOT_SOFTPHONE_ENABLED
        Returned by RegisterTerminalResponse.getCode() if the station administration for the specified extension is not valid for softphone use. Only certain set types are supported and they must be softphone enabled.

      • SHARED_CONTROL_NOT_SUPPORTED

        public static final java.lang.Integer SHARED_CONTROL_NOT_SUPPORTED
        Returned by RegisterFailedEvent.getCode() if the shared control device is not DCP nor an IP phone with speaker.

      • SHARED_CNTRL_INVALID_EXTENSION

        public static final java.lang.Integer SHARED_CNTRL_INVALID_EXTENSION

      • INVALID_STATE

      • INVALID_TERMINAL
